  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (synthetic adversarial: inadequate metrics)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence is reported via R-squared and Pearson correlation coefficients computed against the in-sample calibration dataset used to tune the power-law hemolysis damage model. These statistics are presented as confirmation that the model accurately predicts hemolysis; however, they measure goodness-of-fit on training data and do not address the COU question of interest, which is whether the model correctly ranks worst-case operating conditions for an unseen pump geometry under CPB deployment conditions.",
