      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "R-squared goodness-of-fit on calibration dataset",
      "description": "The hemolysis power-law damage accumulation model was fitted to the Heuser & Optiz (1980) and Paul et al. (2003) in vitro shear-exposure datasets. After parameter optimisation, R² = 0.94 was achieved across 87 calibration data points spanning shear stress 1–450 Pa and exposure times 0.001–1.0 s. This high coefficient of determination demonstrates that the model captures the underlying hemolysis response surface with strong fidelity, supporting its use for ranking operating conditions in the CPB COU. The R² statistic is reported as the primary validation metric confirming model adequacy.",
      "metricName": "R-squared (coefficient of determination)",
      "metricValue": 0.94,
      "metricDataset": "https://uofa.net/synth/data/morrison-calibration-dataset-in-sample",
      "note": "WEAKENER NOTE (inadequate-metrics): R² on the calibration (training) dataset measures how well the power-law model was fitted, not whether the CFD model correctly identifies worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for an unseen pump geometry. The COU question of interest is relative ranking of 5 flow-speed combinations by predicted RH index under deployment conditions; in-sample R² provides no evidence of this capability."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr-02-pearson-shear-stress",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Pearson correlation of predicted vs. measured normalised hemolysis index (calibration cohort)",
      "description": "Pearson correlation coefficient r = 0.97 was computed between CFD-predicted normalised hemolysis index (NHI) values and in vitro measurements drawn from the same calibration cohort used to fit model coefficients. The near-unity correlation is interpreted as strong agreement between model and experiment, providing confidence that the model is suitable for evaluating worst-case operating conditions across the 5 CPB flow-speed combinations. No hold-out or cross-validation dataset was used; the Pearson r is computed over the same observations used during parameter estimation.",
      "metricName": "Pearson correlation coefficient (r)",
      "metricValue": 0.97,
      "metricDataset": "https://uofa.net/synth/data/morrison-calibration-dataset-in-sample",
      "note": "WEAKENER NOTE (inadequate-metrics): Pearson r computed on the calibration cohort is inflated by overfitting and does not measure predictive accuracy on the deployment pump geometry. The COU requires evidence that the model correctly ranks worst-case conditions (RH < 1 criterion) for the FDA generic centrifugal pump under CPB conditions, not that it correlates with the data it was tuned on."
    },
    {
